Updating current version of pyton on linux

Resources
        - https://phoenixnap.com/kb/upgrade-python#ftoc-heading-7

Command sequence:
python3 # check current version of python
sudo apt install python3.9 # specifiy version here
python3.9 # check that binary runs
python3 --version # python symlink should still point to previous version
sudo update-alternatives --config python3 # check current list of symlink alternatives
sudo update-alternatives --install /usr/bin/python3 python3 /usr/bin/python3.8 1 # install first alternative
sudo update-alternatives --install /usr/bin/python3 python3 /usr/bin/python3.9 2 # install second alternative
sudo update-alternatives --config python3 # check updated list of symlink alternatives
sudo rm /usr/bin/python3 # didn't need this - discard old version of python symlink?
sudo ln -s python3.9 /usr/bin/python3 # replace current symlink with new one
python3 --version # check default version

Reinstall pip:
sudo apt install python3.9-venv
python3 -m venv .env

Installing python
        - sudo apt-get install python3.9
        - sudo apt-get install python3.10-venv